# WayPoint agent rules

Always read `AGENTS.md` first. Then load `agent_docs/project_brief.md` for compact context.

## Non-negotiables

- Every itinerary place must have a `rationale` field and at least one `source` reference. Never stub or skip these — they are the core product differentiator.
- Day plans must include travel-time buffers between stops. Never return a day plan that is just a flat list of places with no timing logic.
- No API keys, secrets, or credentials in source code. Use environment variables only.
- No full blog or article text stored in the database. Summaries, metadata, and source links only.
- Do not build features outside MVP scope without explicit approval.

## Workflow

- Propose a plan before writing code. Wait for approval.
- Build one feature at a time. Stop and summarize after each.
- Write a `specs/recap-YYYY-MM-DD.md` at the end of each session.

## Code style

- TypeScript with strict mode. No `any` without justification.
- Small, single-purpose components and functions.
- Comments only for non-obvious intent — not narration of what the code does.
